"inna","kitāba","al-fujāri","lafī","sijjīnin",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,2559],[2,2559,3699],[3,3699,4509],[4,4509,5769],[5,5769,6329],[6,6329,10014]]}},{"name":"83:8","price":" 8. And what will make you know what Sijjîn is?","arabic":"وَمَآ أَدۡرَىٰكَ مَا سِجِّينٞ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5856,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wamā adrāka mā sijjīnun ","translations":["And what","can make you know","what","(is) Sijjin","(8)"],"transliterationArr":["wamā","adrāka","mā","sijjīnun",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,2320],[2,2320,3380],[3,3380,3720],[4,3720,7575]]}},{"name":"83:9","price":" 9. A Register inscribed.","arabic":"كِتَٰبٞ مَّرۡقُومٞ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5857,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"kitābun marqūmun ","translations":["A book","written","(9)"],"transliterationArr":["kitābun","marqūmun",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,910],[2,910,5135]]}},{"name":"83:10","price":" 10. Woe, that Day, to those who deny.","arabic":"وَيۡلٞ يَوۡمَئِذٖ لِّلۡمُكَذِّبِينَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5858,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"waylun yawma-idhin lil'mukadhibīna ","translations":["Woe","that Day","to the deniers","(10)"],"transliterationArr":["waylun","yawma-idhin","lil'mukadhibīna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1680],[2,1680,2660],[3,2660,6475]]}},{"name":"83:11","price":" 11. Those who deny the Day of Recompense.","arabic":"ٱلَّذِينَ يُكَذِّبُونَ بِيَوۡمِ ٱلدِّينِ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5859,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"alladhīna yukadhibūna biyawmi al-dīni ","translations":["Those who","deny","(the) Day","(of) the Judgment","(11)"],"transliterationArr":["alladhīna","yukadhibūna","biyawmi","al-dīni",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1260],[2,1260,2720],[3,2720,3540],[4,3540,6215]]}},{"name":"83:12","price":" 12. And none can deny it except every transgressor beyond bounds, (in disbelief, oppression and disobedience to Allâh) the sinner!","arabic":"وَمَا يُكَذِّبُ بِهِۦٓ إِلَّا كُلُّ مُعۡتَدٍ أَثِيمٍ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5860,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wamā yukadhibu bihi illā kullu muʿ'tadin athīmin ","translations":["And not","can deny","[of] it","except","every","transgressor","sinful","(12)"],"transliterationArr":["wamā","yukadhibu","bihi","illā","kullu","muʿ'tadin","athīmin",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,700],[2,700,1750],[3,1750,3770],[4,3770,4550],[5,4550,5240],[6,5240,6210],[7,6210,9285]]}},{"name":"83:13","price":" 13. When Our Verses (of the Qur’ân) are recited to him he says: \"Tales of the ancients!\"","arabic":"إِذَا تُتۡلَىٰ عَلَيۡهِ ءَايَٰتُنَا قَالَ أَسَٰطِيرُ ٱلۡأَوَّلِينَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5861,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"idhā tut'lā ʿalayhi āyātunā qāla asāṭīru al-awalīna ","translations":["When","are recited","to him","Our Verses","he says","Stories","(of) the former (people)","(13)"],"transliterationArr":["idhā","tut'lā","ʿalayhi","āyātunā","qāla","asāṭīru","al-awalīna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,740],[2,740,1550],[3,1550,2400],[4,2400,3830],[5,3830,4550],[6,4550,5740],[7,5740,9605]]}},{"name":"83:14","price":" 14. Nay! But on their hearts is the Rân (covering of sins and evil deeds) which they used to earn.[1]","arabic":"كَلَّاۖ بَلۡۜ رَانَ عَلَىٰ قُلُوبِهِم مَّا كَانُواْ يَكۡسِبُونَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5862,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"(V.83:14) Narrated Abu Hurairah رضي الله عنه: Allâh’s Messenger صلى الله عليه وسلم said, \"When a slave (a person) commits a sin (an evil deed) a black dot is dotted on his heart. Then if that person gives up that evil deed (sin), begs Allâh to forgive him, and repents, then his heart is cleared (from that heart covering dot); but if he repeats the evil deed (sin), then that covering is increased till his heart is completely covered with it. And that is Ar-Rân which Allâh mentioned (in the Qur’ân), \"Nay! but on their hearts is the Rân (covering of sins and evil deeds) which they used to earn.\" (At-Tirmidhi, Vol.5, Hadith No.3334).","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"kallā bal rāna ʿalā qulūbihim mā kānū yaksibūna ","translations":["Nay","But","(the) stain has covered","[over]","their hearts","(for) what","they used to","earn","(14)"],"transliterationArr":["kallā","bal","rāna","ʿalā","qulūbihim","mā","kānū","yaksibūna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,940],[2,940,1400],[3,1400,2260],[4,2260,2960],[5,2960,4540],[6,4540,5520],[7,5520,6390],[8,6390,9485]]}},{"name":"83:15","price":" 15. Nay! Surely they (evil-doers) will be veiled from seeing their Lord that Day.","arabic":"كَلَّآ إِنَّهُمۡ عَن رَّبِّهِمۡ يَوۡمَئِذٖ لَّمَحۡجُوبُونَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5863,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"kallā innahum ʿan rabbihim yawma-idhin lamaḥjūbūna ","translations":["Nay","Indeed, they","from","their Lord","that Day","surely will be partitioned","(15)"],"transliterationArr":["kallā","innahum","ʿan","rabbihim","yawma-idhin","lamaḥjūbūna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,2490],[2,2490,4080],[3,4080,4320],[4,4320,5570],[5,5570,6730],[6,6730,10635]]}},{"name":"83:16","price":" 16. Then, verily, they will indeed enter (and taste) the burning flame of Hell.","arabic":"ثُمَّ إِنَّهُمۡ لَصَالُواْ ٱلۡجَحِيمِ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5864,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"thumma innahum laṣālū al-jaḥīmi ","translations":["Then","indeed, they","(surely) will burn","(in) the Hellfire","(16)"],"transliterationArr":["thumma","innahum","laṣālū","al-jaḥīmi",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1500],[2,1500,3430],[3,3430,4280],[4,4280,7255]]}},{"name":"83:17","price":" 17. Then, it will be said to them: \"This is what you used to deny!\"","arabic":"ثُمَّ يُقَالُ هَٰذَا ٱلَّذِي كُنتُم بِهِۦ تُكَذِّبُونَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5865,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"thumma yuqālu hādhā alladhī kuntum bihi tukadhibūna ","translations":["Then","it will be said","This","(is) what","you used to","[of it]","deny","(17)"],"transliterationArr":["thumma","yuqālu","hādhā","alladhī","kuntum","bihi","tukadhibūna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1160],[2,1160,2120],[3,2120,2710],[4,2710,3610],[5,3610,5090],[6,5090,6340],[7,6340,6920],[8,6920,10425]]}},{"name":"83:18","price":" 18. Nay! Verily, the Record (writing of the deeds) of Al-Abrâr (the pious believers of Islamic Monotheism) is (preserved) in ‘Illiyyûn","arabic":"كَلَّآ إِنَّ كِتَٰبَ ٱلۡأَبۡرَارِ لَفِي عِلِّيِّينَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5866,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"kallā inna kitāba al-abrāri lafī ʿilliyyīna ","translations":["Nay","Indeed","(the) record","(of) the righteous","(will be) surely in","Illiyin","(18)"],"transliterationArr":["kallā","inna","kitāba","al-abrāri","lafī","ʿilliyyīna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,2320],[2,2320,3620],[3,3620,4420],[4,4420,5770],[5,5770,6380],[6,6380,9705]]}},{"name":"83:19","price":" 19. And what will make you know what ‘Illiyyûn is?","arabic":"وَمَآ أَدۡرَىٰكَ مَا عِلِّيُّونَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5867,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wamā adrāka mā ʿilliyyūna ","translations":["And what","can make you know","what","(is) Illiyun","(19)"],"transliterationArr":["wamā","adrāka","mā","ʿilliyyūna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,2050],[2,2050,3080],[3,3080,3520],[4,3520,7145]]}},{"name":"83:20","price":" 20. A Register inscribed,","arabic":"كِتَٰبٞ مَّرۡقُومٞ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5868,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"kitābun marqūmun ","translations":["A book","written","(20)"],"transliterationArr":["kitābun","marqūmun",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,880],[2,880,4825]]}},{"name":"83:21","price":" 21. To which bear witness those nearest (to Allâh, i.e. the angels).","arabic":"يَشۡهَدُهُ ٱلۡمُقَرَّبُونَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5869,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"yashhaduhu al-muqarabūna ","translations":["Witness it","those brought near","(21)"],"transliterationArr":["yashhaduhu","al-muqarabūna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1030],[2,1030,4615]]}},{"name":"83:22","price":" 22. Verily, Al-Abrâr (the pious believers of Islamic Monotheism) will be in Delight (Paradise).","arabic":"إِنَّ ٱلۡأَبۡرَارَ لَفِي نَعِيمٍ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5870,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"inna al-abrāra lafī naʿīmin ","translations":["Indeed","the righteous","(will be) surely in","bliss","(22)"],"transliterationArr":["inna","al-abrāra","lafī","naʿīmin",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1530],[2,1530,2830],[3,2830,3410],[4,3410,6265]]}},{"name":"83:23","price":" 23. On thrones, looking (at all things).","arabic":"عَلَى ٱلۡأَرَآئِكِ يَنظُرُونَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5871,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"ʿalā al-arāiki yanẓurūna ","translations":["On","thrones","observing","(23)"],"transliterationArr":["ʿalā","al-arāiki","yanẓurūna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,640],[2,640,3379],[3,3379,7274]]}},{"name":"83:24","price":" 24. You will recognise in their faces the brightness of delight.","arabic":"تَعۡرِفُ فِي وُجُوهِهِمۡ نَضۡرَةَ ٱلنَّعِيمِ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5872,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"taʿrifu fī wujūhihim naḍrata al-naʿīmi ","translations":["You will recognize","in","their faces","(the) radiance","(of) bliss","(24)"],"transliterationArr":["taʿrifu","fī","wujūhihim","naḍrata","al-naʿīmi",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,920],[2,920,1330],[3,1330,2680],[4,2680,3480],[5,3480,7065]]}},{"name":"83:25","price":" 25. They will be given to drink of pure sealed wine.","arabic":"يُسۡقَوۡنَ مِن رَّحِيقٖ مَّخۡتُومٍ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5873,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"yus'qawna min raḥīqin makhtūmin ","translations":["They will be given to drink","of","a pure wine","sealed","(25)"],"transliterationArr":["yus'qawna","min","raḥīqin","makhtūmin",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1230],[2,1230,1460],[3,1460,2520],[4,2520,6395]]}},{"name":"83:26","price":" 26. The last thereof (that wine) will be the smell of Musk, and for this let (all) those strive who want to strive (i.e. hasten earnestly to the obedience of Allah).","arabic":"خِتَٰمُهُۥ مِسۡكٞۚ وَفِي ذَٰلِكَ فَلۡيَتَنَافَسِ ٱلۡمُتَنَٰفِسُونَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5874,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"khitāmuhu mis'kun wafī dhālika falyatanāfasi al-mutanāfisūna ","translations":["Its seal","(will be of) musk","And for","that","let aspire","the aspirers","(26)"],"transliterationArr":["khitāmuhu","mis'kun","wafī","dhālika","falyatanāfasi","al-mutanāfisūna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1350],[2,1350,2360],[3,2360,2990],[4,2990,3820],[5,3820,5620],[6,5620,9225]]}},{"name":"83:27","price":" 27. It (that wine) will be mixed with Tasnîm:","arabic":"وَمِزَاجُهُۥ مِن تَسۡنِيمٍ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5875,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wamizājuhu min tasnīmin ","translations":["And its mixture","(is) of","Tasneem","(27)"],"transliterationArr":["wamizājuhu","min","tasnīmin",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1610],[2,1610,2220],[3,2220,5945]]}},{"name":"83:28","price":" 28. A spring whereof drink those nearest to Allâh.","arabic":"عَيۡنٗا يَشۡرَبُ بِهَا ٱلۡمُقَرَّبُونَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5876,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"ʿaynan yashrabu bihā al-muqarabūna ","translations":["A spring","will drink","from it","those brought near","(28)"],"transliterationArr":["ʿaynan","yashrabu","bihā","al-muqarabūna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,680],[2,680,2640],[3,2640,3010],[4,3010,6825]]}},{"name":"83:29","price":" 29. Verily, (during the worldly life) those who committed crimes used to laugh at those who believed.","arabic":"إِنَّ ٱلَّذِينَ أَجۡرَمُواْ كَانُواْ مِنَ ٱلَّذِينَ ءَامَنُواْ يَضۡحَكُونَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5877,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"inna alladhīna ajramū kānū mina alladhīna āmanū yaḍḥakūna ","translations":["Indeed","those who","committed crimes","used to","at","those who","believed","laugh","(29)"],"transliterationArr":["inna","alladhīna","ajramū","kānū","mina","alladhīna","āmanū","yaḍḥakūna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1480],[2,1480,2520],[3,2520,3530],[4,3530,4400],[5,4400,4740],[6,4740,5790],[7,5790,6870],[8,6870,10255]]}},{"name":"83:30","price":" 30. And, whenever they passed by them, used to wink one to another (in mockery).","arabic":"وَإِذَا مَرُّواْ بِهِمۡ يَتَغَامَزُونَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5878,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wa-idhā marrū bihim yataghāmazūna ","translations":["And when","they passed","by them","they winked at one another","(30)"],"transliterationArr":["wa-idhā","marrū","bihim","yataghāmazūna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1000],[2,1000,1800],[3,1800,2380],[4,2380,5765]]}},{"name":"83:31","price":" 31. And when they returned to their own people, they would return jesting;","arabic":"وَإِذَا ٱنقَلَبُوٓاْ إِلَىٰٓ أَهۡلِهِمُ ٱنقَلَبُواْ فَكِهِينَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5879,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wa-idhā inqalabū ilā ahlihimu inqalabū fakihīna ","translations":["And when","they returned","to","their people","they would return","jesting","(31)"],"transliterationArr":["wa-idhā","inqalabū","ilā","ahlihimu","inqalabū","fakihīna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,610],[2,610,3700],[3,3700,5660],[4,5660,6650],[5,6650,8320],[6,8320,11335]]}},{"name":"83:32","price":" 32. And when they saw them, they said: \"Verily these have indeed gone astray!\"","arabic":"وَإِذَا رَأَوۡهُمۡ قَالُوٓاْ إِنَّ هَٰٓؤُلَآءِ لَضَآلُّونَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5880,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wa-idhā ra-awhum qālū inna hāulāi laḍāllūna ","translations":["And when","they saw them","they said","Indeed","these","surely have gone astray","(32)"],"transliterationArr":["wa-idhā","ra-awhum","qālū","inna","hāulāi","laḍāllūna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,840],[2,840,1850],[3,1850,3850],[4,3850,5100],[5,5100,8900],[6,8900,15075]]}},{"name":"83:33","price":" 33. But they (disbelievers, sinners) had not been sent as watchers over them (the believers).","arabic":"وَمَآ أُرۡسِلُواْ عَلَيۡهِمۡ حَٰفِظِينَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5881,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"wamā ur'silū ʿalayhim ḥāfiẓīna ","translations":["But not","they had been sent","over them","(as) guardians","(33)"],"transliterationArr":["wamā","ur'silū","ʿalayhim","ḥāfiẓīna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,2440],[2,2440,3380],[3,3380,4410],[4,4410,7615]]}},{"name":"83:34","price":" 34. But this Day (the Day of Resurrection) those who believe will laugh at the disbelievers[2]","arabic":"فَٱلۡيَوۡمَ ٱلَّذِينَ ءَامَنُواْ مِنَ ٱلۡكُفَّارِ يَضۡحَكُونَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5882,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"(V.83:34) Narrated Anas bin Mâlik رضي الله عنه: A man said, \"O Allâh’s Prophet! Will Allâh gather a disbeliever (prone) on his face on the Day of Resurrection?\" He صلى الله عليه وسلم said, \"Will not the One Who made him walk on his feet in this world, be able to make him walk on his face on the Day of Resurrection?\" (Qatâdah, a subnarrator, said: \"Yes, By the Power of Our Lord!\") (Sahih Al-Bukhari, Vol.6, Hadith No.283).","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"fal-yawma alladhīna āmanū mina al-kufāri yaḍḥakūna ","translations":["So today","those who","believed ","at","the disbelievers","they will laugh","(34)"],"transliterationArr":["fal-yawma","alladhīna","āmanū","mina","al-kufāri","yaḍḥakūna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,1040],[2,1040,2110],[3,2110,3220],[4,3220,3560],[5,3560,4770],[6,4770,8485]]}},{"name":"83:35","price":"35. On (high) thrones, looking (at all things).","arabic":"عَلَى ٱلۡأَرَآئِكِ يَنظُرُونَ","category":["83 (Al-Mutaffifin)","Al-Mutaffifin","Surah Al-Mutaffifin"],"ayahNumber":5883,"juzNumber":30,"footnotes":"","lang":"en","meta":{"transliteration":"ʿalā al-arāiki yanẓurūna ","translations":["On","the thrones","observing","(35)"],"transliterationArr":["ʿalā","al-arāiki","yanẓurūna",null],"verseTiming":[[1,0,490],[2,490,3290],[3,3290,7695]]}},{"name":"83:36","price":" 36. Are not the disbelievers paid (fully) for what they used to do?","arabic":"هَلۡ ثُوِّبَ ٱلۡكُفَّارُ